Follow-up to the 0013-0017 audio-refactor cluster (#31). Wires the SFX
volume slider that 0017 left as a deliberate TODO and 0014 was supposed
to deliver but missed. Caught by nxengine's synthesis-correctness review
of the audio cluster (#31 review pass).

Numbered 0014a so it sorts between 0014 (the Pixtone Mix→MIX + 64-track
pool) and 0015 (Organya) in `find | sort` lexical order — keeps apply-
patches.sh's apply-in-numeric-order behavior consistent with the natural
dependency: 0014a needs 0014's _track_pool present and 0017's
SoundManager::updateSfxVolume hook.

================================================================
The gap
================================================================

Upstream: SoundManager::updateSfxVolume() → Mix_Volume(-1, (int)(128.0/
100.0 * sfx_volume)). Effective SDL2 gain = sfx_volume_0_100 / 100.

Migration (in 0017): SoundManager::updateSfxVolume() → no-op TODO with
comment "wired in patch 0014: Pixtone::getInstance()->setVolume(...)".

Migration (in 0014): track-pool added, but Pixtone::setVolume method
NOT added, and SoundManager::updateSfxVolume left as the 0017 TODO.

Net effect: SFX plays at full gain regardless of the user's settings
slider. Music volume preserved correctly by 0016; SFX is the missed
sibling. Functional regression vs upstream.

================================================================
The fix
================================================================

1. Pixtone::setVolume(int volume_0_100) — new public method on Pixtone
   that iterates the 64-track _track_pool calling MIX_SetTrackGain
   with gain = volume_0_100 / 100.0f. NULL pool entries skipped (a
   track allocation could have failed at init time without being
   fatal). Conversion preserves upstream's effective gain exactly:

     upstream: Mix_Volume(-1, 128/100 * vol)
               → SDL2 effective gain = (128/100 * vol) / 128 = vol/100
     ours:     MIX_SetTrackGain(track, vol/100.0f)
               → SDL3 effective gain = vol/100

   Audio-capture A/B at Phase 7 gate stays interpretable.

2. SoundManager::updateSfxVolume() — body changed from no-op TODO to
   call Pixtone::getInstance()->setVolume(settings->sfx_volume).

3. Pixtone::play() — `// DOS-PORT:` comment block added documenting
   the synchronous-callback dependency (MIX_StopTrack on a playing
   track may dispatch the per-track stopped-callback inline before
   returning, which is sequential on DJGPP cooperative scheduler but
   would race on multi-threaded hosts). Race is benign in practice
   (old slot reset to -1 is correct regardless), but the logic relies
   on synchronous dispatch for clarity. References docs/SDL3-MIGRATION
   § 3 invariant.

================================================================
Bug-find credit reframe (per nxengine's review)
================================================================

nxengine's review noted that 0014's "side fix" framing of the Pixtone::
shutdown variable-shadowing typo undersells it. The bug:

  for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= NUM_SOUNDS; i++) {
    ...
    for (int i = 0; i < NUM_RESAMPLED_BUFFERS; i++) {  // ← inner i
      if (_sound_fx[i].resampled[i]) { Mix_FreeChunk... }
                  // ↑ shadowed inner i, not outer SFX-slot index
    }
  }

The inner `i` shadows the outer SFX-slot iterator. Net behavior under
SDL2_mixer: most resampled buffers leaked at process exit (slots 16..
NUM_SOUNDS never got their resampled[] freed), some slots' resampled
buffers got considered with the wrong index. Harmless on SDL2_mixer
because Mix_FreeChunk on null was a no-op after the first cleanup
pass and the OS reclaimed the leaks at exit.

Under SDL3_mixer post-migration, the equivalent MIX_DestroyAudio on
a stale pointer would be a hard double-free that the new allocator
won't tolerate as gracefully. 0014's fix (rename inner to `j`,
access _sound_fx[i].resampled[j] correctly) was therefore not
optional polish — it was load-bearing for the migration not crashing
on shutdown.

This is a meaningful upstream-find-during-migration win in the lineage
of nxengine's #30 SDL_Init-bool-return / SDL_GetBasePath-const finds.
Ratifying nxengine's "Path B's hypothesis paying out" framing here
since 0014 is already committed; rebasing the cluster mid-stack to
edit 0014's commit body for credit attribution would be more risk
than benefit.

================================================================
Why follow-up patch instead of amending 0014 + 0017
================================================================

Per team-lead's option B selection: amending 0014 + 0017 mid-stack
would require rebasing 5 commits in the audio cluster topic branch.
Rebase risk on already-reviewed code exceeds the value of compacting
the volume wireup into 0014. 0014a is the clean separation: small,
atomic, post-cluster, lands as a single follow-up patch in build-
engineer's next commit cycle.

================================================================
Validation
================================================================

Build verification deferred to build-engineer's next `make nxengine`
attempt (currently #40 / Phase 5). Expected post-build behavior:
- Title screen: SFX (e.g. menu cursor at default sfx_volume=100) at
  full gain, equivalent to upstream.
- Settings menu: SFX volume slider adjusts effective SFX level
  proportionally (upstream behavior: 0..100 maps to 0..1.0 gain).
  Pre-0014a: slider has no effect.
- Audio-capture A/B at Phase 7 gate: SFX levels match pre-migration
  capture at any given sfx_volume setting.

================================================================
Touch points
================================================================

- src/sound/Pixtone.h: +13 lines (public setVolume declaration + comment)
- src/sound/Pixtone.cpp: +47 lines (setVolume definition + Pixtone::play
  synchronous-callback DOS-PORT comment)
- src/sound/SoundManager.cpp: -8 lines / +5 lines (replaces no-op TODO
  body with Pixtone::setVolume call; comment trimmed since the rationale
  now lives at the receiving end)

Total ~57 lines net addition, no new external dependencies, no new
public API beyond Pixtone::setVolume.
